-- CANADA RESEARCH ROUNDUP: Norbord, Blackpearl Resources 
-- 
-- Fri Jan 31, 2014 06:16AM EST
-- None



Jan 31 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several Canadian companies, including Norbord and Blackpearl Resources, on Friday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Norbord <NBD.TO>: Raymond James raises to outperform from market perform * Blackpearl Resources <PXX.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises to buy from hold  Following is a summary of research actions on Canadian companies reported by Reuters on Friday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order. See bottom of the table for sector changes.* Bank of Nova Scotia <BNS.TO>: Citigroup raises target to C$66 from C$62; rating neutral * Bell Canada <BCE.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises target to C$47 from C$45; rating hold * Blackpearl Resources <PXX.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises to buy from hold * Blackpearl Resources <PXX.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises target to C$3.50 from C$2.75 * Canadian National Railway <CNR.TO>: Canaccord ups target to C$60.50 from C$58; hold  * Corus Entertainment <CJRb.TO>: Barclays ups target to C$25 from C$24, rating equal weight  * Exco Technologies <XTC.TO>: Canaccord Genuity ups target to C$9.25 from C$9; rating buy * HudBay Minerals <HBM.TO>: Canaccord Genuity cuts target to C$11.50 from C$12; rating buy * HudBay Minerals <HBM.TO>: CIBC cuts target to C$11 from C$12; rating sector outperformer  * Imperial Oil <IMO.TO>: Barclays raises target price to C$55 from C$50, rating overweight  * MBAC Fertilizer <MBC.TO>: Canaccord cuts target to C$1.85 from C$2.75;speculativebuy * Norbord <NBD.TO>: Raymond James raises to outperform from market perform * Norbord <NBD.TO>: CIBC cuts target price to C$34 from C$37; rating sector outperformer